main event: Unidentified flying objects were sighted near Rockledge, Florida on February 15, 1950.
interesting points: Witnesses observed 4 to 13 slow moving objects that appeared to behave erratically, different from birds., A witness driving on U.S. 1 reported seeing long, slender, white objects moving northward., Additional reports pointed to a total of six brilliantly-white moving objects., The investigation concluded the objects were probably balloons, yet this was uncertain., Another resident described intense light illuminating the area around their car.
witness description: One witness was a Rockledge resident driving on U.S. 1, accompanied by four others in the car.
